highnumber

Class HighNumber

  • java.lang.Object
    • highnumber.HighNumber

  • public class HighNumber
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for mathematical operations. Number arguments in this class are mostly String type, like "12", "-0.123" or "19283764.12963897163".
    Important - decimal separator for this class is . (dot). Highest precision of calculations is returned by getPrecision(), can be changed by setPrecision(). It is STRONGLY recommended to check correct format of input numbers before computing by isNumber(String) method.

      • beforeAfter

        public int[] beforeAfter(java.lang.String input)
        beforeAfter

        public int[] beforeAfter(String input)

        Tells how many digits are before and after decimal separator. It does not include minus. If number is not decimal number there would be 0 as result after decimal separator. Correct format of input number should be checked before by isNumber(String) method.
        Parameters:
        input - number to be processed.
        Returns:
        [x, y] int table where x is number of digits before decimal separator and y is number of digits after decimal separator.

      • evenBeforeAfter

        public java.lang.String[] evenBeforeAfter(java.lang.String numA,
                                          java.lang.String numB)
        evenBeforeAfter

        public String[] evenBeforeAfter(String numA, String numB)

        Makes even amount of digits before and after decimal separator in both numbers by adding zeros before first and last number. If number is not decimal number a '.0' will be added to number before processing. Negative numbers are turned into absolute version before processing as well. Correct format of input numbers should be checked before by isNumber(String) method.
        Parameters:
        numA - first number to be processed.
        numB - second number to be processed.
        Returns:
        numbers with the same amount of digits before and after decimal separator in String table form ([numA,numB]).

      • round

        public java.lang.String round(java.lang.String input,
                              int innerPrec)
                       throws HighNumberException
        round

        public String round(String input, int innerPrec) throws HighNumberException

        Rounds number with given precision. If given precision is greater than precision returned by getPrecision(), number is rounded to precision returned by getPrecision(), also if number is not decimal then not-decimal form of number is returned. Correct format of input number should be checked before by isNumber(String) method.
        Parameters:
        input - number to be rounded.
        innerPrec - precision to be used.
        Returns:
        rounded number.
        Throws:
        HighNumberException - default exception for highnumber.HighNumber.
